  <section id="history">
    <h2>Our History</h2>
    <p>
      SHASA grew from the Adventist student movement in PNG, which began in the early 1980s. In 1984, PNGATSA was
      established to provide spiritual support, leadership development, and fellowship for Adventist students in
      tertiary institutions.
    </p>
    <p>
      Recognizing the unique needs of students in the Southern Highlands, SHASA was formed as a provincial association.
      It became a place where students could stay connected to their faith, build meaningful friendships, and engage
      in service and leadership opportunities while studying away from home.
    </p>
  </section>

